hopobject.body: Punk not dead gabrielavillarreal.com It would also be the Bloomberg speech where he claimed that after the 1931 ‘Austerity” budget unemployment rose, debt rose and Britain faced years of low growth, whereas, the record shows that within a year economic contraction turned into growth (which accelerated thereafter, remaining above, often well above, 3% until 1938), unemployment stabilised and then started to fall and debt stabilized and later fell as a proportion of GDP.
